commentTextItems.html: and he brings up the victory with a sweet drive through the covers

commentPostTextItems.html: So Bangladesh win easily by 6 wickets in the end. Ireland's total never looked like being enough and so it proved thanks mainly to Tamim.
The man of the match has been announced and it has been given to Shafiul Islam who took four crucial wickets in the first innings.
So the series ends 1-1 and both sides will be able to take positives from the two days. Thanks for joining us and from Conor Hayes in Stormount it's goodbye.

commentTextItems.html: tries to smash it but does not connect properly
tapped into the legside for a single
another drive through the covers to bring Bangladesh closer

stories.title: Tamim, Shafiul help Bangladesh square series
stories.subTitle: Ireland v Bangladesh, 2nd ODI, Belfast
stories.seoTitle: Ireland v Bangladesh: Tamim, Shafiul help Bangladesh square series
stories.summary: After a disappointing show in the first game, Bangladesh's bowlers hit back with a disciplined performance to restrict Ireland to 189 and set up a six-wicket win to draw the series 1-1 at Stormont
